description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directorate of Specialised Medicine &amp; Communicable Diseases&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Joint Consultant in Infectious Diseases, Tropical Medicine &amp; Acute Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications are invited for one full time Joint Consultant post in Acute Medicine and Infectious Diseases to commence as soon as possible. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This appointment is ideal for physicians accredited in General (Internal) Medicine and Infectious Diseases. This is time tested as we already have multiple joint appointment posts within these two specialties delivering successful patient care and excellent clinical outcomes. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The appointee will be expected to take part in undergraduate and postgraduate teaching and training. Research is encouraged and full facilities are available to support this.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full GMC registration is required, together with Membership of the Royal College of Physicians (UK) or equivalent. Applicants are required to hold a CCT or equivalent in General (Internal) Medicine and Infectious Diseases, or to be within six months of being eligible for the CCT. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Should any further vacancies arise, shortlisted candidates will be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Non-UK/EEA applicants should ensure they are aware of the recent changes to the Immigration rules. For further information on how this may affect your application visit the UK Government website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants experiencing problems applying, please contact Medical HR Department, telephone 0114 271 2525 quoting reference 190-STH-20-206&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameClaire Gardner or Ben StoneAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;telephone (0114) 2266955 or e-mail &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;claire.gardner14@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; (for Acute Medcine), &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;benjamin.stone1@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; (for Infectious Diseases).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
